FBIS4-35860 "drnes108_l_94003" FBIS-NES-94-108 Daily Report 5 Jun 1994 ISRAEL Rabin Denies U.S. Intervention Ended Rocket Attacks Rabin Denies U.S. Intervention Ended Rocket Attacks TA0506184494 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in Hebrew 1700 GMT 5 Jun 94 TA0506184494 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network Hebrew BFN [Excerpt] A Syrian appeal to Iran was the factor that stopped the Hizballah Katyusha volleys last weekend, diplomatic sources in Damascus said. The Syrians intervened after receiving an Israeli message via the United States. [passage omitted] [A report on Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network in Hebrew at 1700 GMT on 5 June adds: "The prime minister says the calm on Israel's northern border and the absence of Katyusha rockets had been achieved even before the Americans approached Syria with a demand to curb Hizballah. Our political correspondent Gadi Sukenik reports that the prime minister made these remarks at today's cabinet meeting."]
